
[1]polyglot

   POL'YGLOT, a. [Gr. many, and tongue.] Having or containing many
   languages; as a polyglot lexicon or Bible.

   POL'YGLOT, n. A book containing many languages, particularly the Bible
   containing the Scriptures in several languages.

   1. One who understands many languages. [Not in use.]
